text:
Mäntä-Vilppula is a town and a municipality located in Finland. It was formed in 2009, when two municipalities, Mänttä and Vilppula, joined together. It is in the Pirkanmaa region.
The town has a population of 9,978 (31 January 2019). It covers an area of 657.08 square kilometers.
Next to it are the municipalities of Keuruu, Juupajoki, Jämsä, Ruovesi and Virrat.
